<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-134-730  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 134 730.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  March 1 1989 v28 n5 p22(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sweeping SCSI revision finally approaches standardization. (smallcomputer systems interface) (includes related articles on SCSI-2performance and SCSI-3)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lieberman, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>After two years of development, Ciprico introduces the firstSCSI-2 host adaptor called the 3550 Rimfire VMEbus.andP;  The interfacesystem had been expected earlier but the project had gotten out ofhand, partly because, rather than simply improving on SCSI-1, thewhole standard was revised.andP;  The original intention was to limitthe number of 'vendor-unique' functions allowed by SCSI-1 becausethey defeated the independence and interoperability which thatstandard was supposed to provide.andP;  In an effort to achieve this,however, SCSI-2 has become four times the size of the earlierdocument, and is criticized by many as being too unwieldy to be ofpractical use to the average user.andP;  The 'wide' and 'fast' optionsoffered by SCSI-2 have met with a similarly mixed reaction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ciprico Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    CPCI.andO;Product:   Ciprico 3550 Rimfire VMEbus (Circuit board) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Small Computer Systems InterfaceStandardizationInterfaceInteractive SystemsCompatibilityBuses.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>